  "text": "A second implication is that measurement of intra-tumor heterogeneity may help inform treatment choices, not just provide prognostic information. Results to date in HNSCC suggest that the relation of MATH to outcome may be most striking when standard systemic therapy is part of initial treatment, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] consistent either with selection of preexisting resistance mutations or with a tendency to develop mutations that may lead to resistance in high-heterogeneity tumors. If MATH is highly related to systemic therapy outcome but not so strongly to surgical outcome, high-heterogeneity tumors might preferentially be treated with surgery if there is a choice.",
